ProtoDefines:
. "Let $X$ be a real-valued random variable with density 
   function $f(x)$. The {expected value\/} $\mu = E(X)$ is 
   defined by $$ \mu = E(X) = \int_{-\infty}^{+\infty} xf(x) 
   dx\ , $$ provided the integral $$ \int_{-\infty}^{+\infty} 
   |x|f(x) dx $$ is finite."
